Class BinnedNumericDataset

    • com.github.tm.stindex.spatial.sfc.data.BinnedNumericDataset

    public class BinnedNumericDataset
extends java.lang.Object
implements MultiDimensionalNumericData
    The Binned Numeric Dataset class creates an object that associates a multi-dimensional index range to a particular bin ID.

      • applyBins

        public static java.util.List<BinnedNumericDataset> applyBins(MultiDimensionalNumericData numericData,
                                                             NumericDimensionDefinition[] dimensionDefinitions)
        This method is responsible for translating a query into appropriate normalized and binned (if necessary) queries that can be used by the underlying index implementation. For example, for unbounded dimensions such as time, an incoming query of July 2012 to July 2013 may get translated into 2 binned queries representing the 2012 portion of the query and the 2013 portion, each normalized to millis from the beginning of the year.
        Parameters:
        numericData - the incoming query into the index implementation, to be translated into normalized, binned queries
        dimensionDefinitions - the definition for the dimensions
        Returns:
        normalized indexes
